- Biometric data typically includes physiological measurements such as heart rate, blood oxygen saturation, temperature, etc.; 
- Alerts in this context likely refer to notifications or flags raised when certain thresholds (e.g., high heart rate, low oxygen saturation) are crossed, indicating potential health issues;
- The delay between data collection and alert creation could be critical in assessing the timeliness and effectiveness of the alert system.

sql:
SELECT patient_id, date, vital_signs
FROM health_records
WHERE created_at = (
  SELECT MAX(created_at)
  FROM health_records
);
